us.ihmc.euclid.referenceFrame.interfaces

Interface FrameOrientation2DReadOnly

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Orientation2DReadOnly, ReferenceFrameHolder
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    FixedFrameOrientation2DBasics, FrameOrientation2DBasics
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    FrameOrientation2D

    public interface FrameOrientation2DReadOnly
extends Orientation2DReadOnly, ReferenceFrameHolder
    Read-only interface for a 2D orientation that is expressed in a immutable reference frame.

    A 2D orientation is in the XY-plane, i.e. the yaw angle about the z-axis.

        default double difference(FrameOrientation2DReadOnly other)
        Computes and returns the difference between this and other:
        distance = this.yaw - other.yaw
        Parameters:
        other - the other orientation 2D. Not modified.
        Returns:
        the difference between this and other contained in [-pi, pi].
        Throws:
        ReferenceFrameMismatchException - if other is not expressed in the same frame as this.

        distance = Math.abs(this.yaw - other.yaw)
        Parameters:
        other - the other orientation 2D. Not modified.
        Returns:
        the distance between this and other contained in [0, pi].
        Throws:
        ReferenceFrameMismatchException - if other is not expressed in the same frame as this.

      • transform

        default void transform(FixedFrameTuple3DBasics tupleToTransform)
        Transforms the given tupleToTransform by the rotation about the z-axis described by this. 
                            / cos(yaw) -sin(yaw) 0 \
 tupleToTransform = | sin(yaw)  cos(yaw) 0 | * tupleToTransform
                    \    0         0     1 /
        Parameters:
        tupleToTransform - the tuple to transform. Modified.
        Throws:
        ReferenceFrameMismatchException - if reference frame of this and tupleToTransform do not match.

      • epsilonEquals

        default boolean epsilonEquals(FrameOrientation2DReadOnly other,
                              double epsilon)
        Tests if the yaw angle of this orientation is equal to an epsilon to the yaw of other.

        Note that this method performs number comparison and not an angle comparison, such that: -pi ≠ pi.

        If the two orientations have different frames, this method returns false.

        Parameters:
        other - the query. Not modified.
        epsilon - the tolerance to use.
        Returns:
        true if the two orientations are equal and are expressed in the same reference frame, false otherwise.

      • geometricallyEquals

        default boolean geometricallyEquals(FrameOrientation2DReadOnly other,
                                    double epsilon)
        Compares this to other to determine if the two orientations are geometrically similar, i.e. the difference in yaw of this and other is less than or equal to epsilon.
        Parameters:
        other - the orientation to compare to. Not modified.
        epsilon - the tolerance of the comparison.
        Returns:
        true if the two orientations represent the same geometry, false otherwise.
        Throws:
        ReferenceFrameMismatchException - if other is not expressed in the same frame as this.

      • equals

        default boolean equals(FrameOrientation2DReadOnly other)
        Tests if this orientation 2D is exactly equal to other.

        Note that this method performs number comparison and not an angle comparison, such that: -pi ≠ pi.

        Parameters:
        other - the other orientation 2D to compare against this. Not modified.
        Returns:
        true if the two orientations are exactly equal component-wise and are expressed in the same reference frame, false otherwise.
